==English==
===Etymology===
Latin  exigēns, exigent- present participle of exigere, to [[demand]].

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ēk'sə-jənt/

===Adjective===
'''exigent'''
# [[urgent]]; needing [[immediate]] [[action]]
# [[demanding]]; needing great [[effort]]

===Translations===
*French: [[exigeant]] ([[exacting]]), [[urgent]], [[pressant]]
*Spanish: [[exigente]] ([[demanding]], exacting, [[fussy]], [[particular]], [[strict]]).